The paper presents an alternative foundation for decision making that uses syntactic programs as the primitive objects of choice. This approach is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), game theory (cs.GT), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper's focus on decision making and preference relations suggests that cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely categories, followed by cs.GT, cs.DS, and cs.SY.
